<br>
I think this is the sentence that got me going. I think why you got a big reaction was because most of SAHM feel like constantly need to prove ourselves. I think to a certain degree that at least for me I take a lot of flack from people for my choice. They can’t imagine why I would choose to SAH. They treat me as if what I do is not hard work or is less important than making money. I always get comments like &quot;I don’t know why you are tired or complaining, I would love to be home all day relaxing and playing with my kids&quot; That gets on my last fucking nerve. Makes me crazy that people think that you sit on your ass all day and the kids just magically get all their needs met. (I realize you didn’t say that.) I don’t have an issue with people who have to work or even want work part-time. I do get annoyed at people who know from the get go that there is no way they would ever want to stay home with there kids even if they could and *choose* from the beginning to put there kids in daycare. To me what is the point of having kids. <br>
<br>
Anyway that is my preggo nervous breakdown for the day!!!!<br>
<br>
Leah<br>
