That's a good point Leah, something I was thinking about that gets on my last nerve...workaholics who choose to bring children into this world, but the minute they are born they are thrown into childcare 50-60 hours a week.  Not the parents who have to work just to make ends meet, but the ones who choose their careers over their children...why have children in the first place?<br>
<br>
Once in awhile I get the urge to get back out there into the working force.  But then I slap myself right out of it.  What am I, nuts?  I'm doing what I love and what I've always wanted to do.  <br>
